webpackJsonp([50625364660565],{270:function(e,t){e.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<h1>Badges</h1>\n<p>Badges are used to show notifications and other alerts related to a particular element. Badges do not stand alone, but are combined with text, icons or buttons to show a change or action related to that feature. For example, a badge beside your Inbox link to show the number of unread emails.</p>\n<p>When coding badges, the alternative text that will be read by screen readers should also include context. For example, the badge should read "40 unread emails" instead of just "40".</p>\n<p>Badges in this design system appear as follows:</p>\n<p><img src="./badges.png"></p>\n<p>Rectangle with a width of <strong>28px</strong> and height of <strong>19px</strong>. Border radius of <strong>8px</strong>. Background colour of #4D5D6C. Text colour of #FFFFFF. Text is centred within the rectangle.</p>',frontmatter:{date:null,path:"/component/badges",title:"My first badge post"}}},pathContext:{}}}});
